---
source: starstream-compiler/src/typecheck/tests.rs
description: "Source:\n\nutxo Counter {\n    storage {\n        let mut counter: i64;\n    }\n\n    main fn update(nextCounter: i64) {\n        let _tmp = disclose(counter);\n        counter = nextCounter;\n    }\n}\n"
---
W0001 (https://starstream.nightstream.dev/warnings/W0001)

  ! `disclose(...)` is unnecessary because the wrapped value is already public
   ,-[test.star:7:20]
 6 |     main fn update(nextCounter: i64) {
 7 |         let _tmp = disclose(counter);
   :                    ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^
 8 |         counter = nextCounter;
   `----
  help: `disclose(...)` is redundant because the wrapped value is already public.
E0045 (https://starstream.nightstream.dev/errors/E0045)

  x public binding `counter` requires a public RHS; wrap private values with `disclose(...)`
   ,-[test.star:8:19]
 7 |         let _tmp = disclose(counter);
 8 |         counter = nextCounter;
   :                   ^^^^^^^^^^^
 9 |     }
   `----
  help: `nextCounter` is a private parameter; declare it as `pub nextCounter: ...` in the function signature if callers should provide a public value here.
